The Company’s investments at December 31, 2022 and 2021 carried investment grade credit
ratings. Variable rate demand notes (“VRDNs”) are floating rate municipal bonds with embedded put
options that allow the bondholder to sell the security at par plus accrued interest. All of the put options are
secured by a pledged liquidity source. While they are classified as marketable investment securities, the
put option allows the VRDNs to be liquidated at par on a same day, or more generally, on a seven-day
settlement basis.
