Restricted Stock Units and Performance Share Units
The cost of stock-based compensation for restricted stock units and performance share units is
measured based on the closing fair market value of the Company’s common stock at the date of grant. In
the event that the Company has the option and intent to settle a restricted stock unit or performance share
unit in cash, the award is classified as a liability and revalued at each balance sheet date.
